Andy Turner: Ex-European hurdles champion reflects on career
Media playback is not supported on this deviceHurdler Andy Turner reflects on his career in athletics with BBC London and predicts that British sprinting is entering a "golden era" as he prepares to run his final race at the Great North CityGames in Gateshead on Saturday,The 33-year-old, who lives and trains in Sutton, wonEuropeanandCommonwealth goldin the 110m hurdles in 2010.Turner, who competed in three Olympics and alsowon bronze at the World Championships in 2011,says he has done far more than he could ever imagine in the sport.